1 following:
2 (a) The schools within the district that share a school nurse, if any;
3 (b) If a school has a nurse practicing within the school, how many nurses the
4 school has and if they are stationed full time or part time within the school;
5 (c) The number of schools in the district without a nurse;
6 (d) If the nurses are employed or contracted by the district;
7 (e) The licensure type of each nurse; and
8 (f) The percentage of costs paid by the school district, identifying each of the
9 funding sources utilized, for the district to maintain each nurse;
10 (g) The teacher-to-student ratio of each school; and
11 (h) The nurse-to-student ratio of each school.
